{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Ammand et al. [1] were the first to apply federated learning to collaborative filtering.",
    "Since then, numerous studies have emerged to improve recommendation accuracy [19,27,28], training efficiency [63], and system trustworthiness [60,64].",
    "Some work transplant FedRecs to specific recommendations, such as news recommendation [57], social recommendation [30], POI recommendation [31], and so on [18].",
    "Additionally, some studies have explored incorporating advanced neural networks to enhance FedRecs, such as federated graph-based recommender systems [54] and federated sequential recommender systems [29].Recently, the development of large language models [26] has inspired researchers to harness their power in FedRecs.",
    "For example, Zhao et al. [65] straightforwardly utilized the current FedRec framework to train LLM-based recommender systems."
  ],
